nd family work, and community service are. Focusing on the circumstances of producing a holy black female personhood, Casselberry reveals the ways twenty-first-century women's spiritual power operates and resonates with meaning in Pentecostal, female-majority, male-led churches.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Sep 2020) 0aAfrican American Pentecostals. 0aAfrican American churcheszNew York (State)zNew York. 0aAfrican American women in church work. 0aAfrican American womenxReligious life. 0aChurch of Our Lord Jesus Christ of the Apostolic Faith. 4aPneuma Book Award Winner. 4aSociety for Pentecostal Studies Book Award Winners. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / African American Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK eBook-Package 2017z978311069634940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822372974zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822372974423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822372974.jpg  a978-3-11-069634-9  DUK eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles